Hi Sam,

You wrote,

&quot;John the Baptist gladly embraced Jesus as the one who would usher in the glorious and irresistible coming of the kingdom (John 1:29).&quot;

But that verse says nothing of the kingdom directly, but rather, &quot;The next day he saw Jesus coming toward him, and said, &quot;Behold, the Lamb of God, who takes away the sin of the world!&quot;

Aren&#039;t you front loading your theology of the kingdom into your critique, from texts that weren&#039;t written to teach it? One might be justified for wondering why you cite the gospel of John as teaching a theology of the kingdom when it doesn&#039;t appear to be a prominent feature in the 4th gospel, since the word appears but three times in twenty-two chapters.
